All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
DataManager
This class handles data management for the application, including updating the CSV files for students, supervisors, FYP coordinators, and projects.
DisplayAll
Class for UI purposes to display requests
FYPCoordinator
Child Class of Supervisor that used to represent a FYPCoordinator (because a FYPCoordinator is a supervisor)
IndexGenerator
The IndexGenerator class provides functionality for generating unique index values for project ID.
InitializeApplication
The InitializeApplication class is responsible for loading data from CSV files and initializing the application with the loaded data.
Project
A class that represents a project.
ProjectStatus
This class provides the enum value of possible status of a project
Request
The Request class is an abstract class representing requests sent between users, specifically between a user (student) and a supervisor regarding projects.
RequestChangeProjectTitle
This class represents the "Change Project Title" request type that can be made by student to Supervisor extends from StudentRequest class
RequestChangeSupervisor
Represents a request to change the supervisor of a project.
RequestDeregistration
A class representing a request to deregister a student from a project.
RequestProjectAllocation
Represents a request to change the supervisor of a project.
RequestStatus
This class provides the enum value of possible status of a request
Student
Child Class of users that used to represent a student
StudentRequest
The abstract class representing a student request.
StudentRequestWithString
Abstract class representing a student request with a string-based new project title
Supervisor
Child Class of users that used to represent a supervisor
SupervisorRequest
Parent Class of all possible requests than can be made by a supervisor, extends from Request class
